%% Diagram: Audio chunked streaming over HTTP range requests
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Player as Player (client)
    participant CDN as Audio CDN (Akamai / CloudFront)
    participant Origin as GCS audio origin

    Note over Player: User taps Play
    Player->>CDN: GET /track/{id}/q160.ogg<br/>Range: bytes=0-524287 (512 KB)
    CDN-->>Player: 206 Partial Content (chunk #1)
    Note over Player: First audio frame decoded → playback starts (sub-second TTFB)

    loop While buffer < high watermark (~30 s)
        Player->>CDN: Range: bytes=N-N+524287
        CDN-->>Player: 206 Partial Content
    end

    Note over Player: Current track ~90% complete
    Player->>CDN: GET /track/{next_id}/q160.ogg<br/>Range: bytes=0-524287 (prefetch)
    CDN-->>Player: 206 Partial Content (next track head)

    Note over Player,CDN: TCP/BBR keeps send rate near measured bandwidth<br/>so packet loss does not collapse throughput

    alt Cache miss at edge
        CDN->>Origin: GET object (signed)
        Origin-->>CDN: bytes
    end
